                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12479476" author="mkutty" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2007 01:23:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the first patch for this test conversion. There may be a lot of room for improvement, which I might have missed. So please review this patch and all your comments are very welcome. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12479484" author="djd" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2007 02:36:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would it make sense to add these fixtures to the existing CursorTest since I assume they are testing cursors?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12479485" author="djd" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2007 02:50:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what the method checkResultSet() is trying to check. It&apos;s comments don&apos;t really match its code.&lt;br/&gt;
There are already a series of assert for ResultSets in the JDBC utility class, could one of those work instead.&lt;br/&gt;
If not, then checkResultSet() needs to be cleaned up, e.g. at the moment if null is passed in then the assert will pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Holdability is supported in JSR169 and JDBC 3, basically all environments Derby runs in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rather than use a test specific HaveDriverManager the test should be using JDBC.vmSupportsJDBC3() since DriverManager is a feature of JDBC 3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12479705" author="mkutty" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2007 20:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review , Dan. I don&apos;t have any problem in adding these fixtures to the CursorTest. If that is a better choice then i would do so. Also there is one test called holdCursorjavareflection.java which is specifically for jdk13 with reflection. since we are moving towards jdk1.4 and above, do we still have to have that test? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12480879" author="mkutty" created="Wed, 14 Mar 2007 19:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching new patch which will take care of most of the comments. Still I&apos;m not sure about adding these fixtures to CursorTest. Please review and post your comments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12481752" author="mkutty" created="Fri, 16 Mar 2007 20:21:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to attach the _Suite.java .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12482572" author="kmarsden" created="Tue, 20 Mar 2007 22:34:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Manjula, &lt;br/&gt;
Could you sync up and regenerate the patch.  The 03_16.txt patch does not seem to have the new file and it&apos;s _Suite change is out of date.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12482599" author="mkutty" created="Tue, 20 Mar 2007 23:31:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the new patch. Please review and if looks good please commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12482956" author="kmarsden" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2007 23:14:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Manjula for the patch.  Below are my comments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed we are not running the new HoldCursorTest does not run on JSR169. It seems like we could run all the fixtures except testStatementsInProcedure with JSR169.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In suite() I think the following lines have no effect and can be removed.&lt;br/&gt;
 	TestSuite suite = new TestSuite(&quot;HoldCursorTest&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
            	suite.addTestSuite(HoldCursorTest.class);&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;there are several lines like:&lt;br/&gt;
assertTrue(11== rs2.getInt(1));&lt;br/&gt;
which might be clearer written as &lt;br/&gt;
assertEquals(11,rs2.getInt(1);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And just a nit.  The utility methods for createStatement, setHoldability, and setTransactionIsolation, seem a bit much since they are one line, but it is fine to leave them how they are.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483243" author="mkutty" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2007 17:49:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review, Kathey. Here is the new patch which will fix most of the issues you pointed. Please review and if looks good please commit&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483318" author="kmarsden" created="Thu, 22 Mar 2007 20:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed this patch with a few additional changes to the .runall files that needed to be updated.&lt;br/&gt;
I think though that this will still not run under JSR169 because of this conditional&lt;br/&gt;
	  if ( !JDBC.vmSupportsJDBC3())&lt;br/&gt;
	            return new TestSuite(&quot;empty HoldCursorTest - supported only from JDBC3.0 and above&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that can be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12483639" author="kmarsden" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2007 15:52:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed patch.  Still need additional change to enable for JSR169&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12484504" author="myrna" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2007 18:16:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I adjusted this for JSR169, tested, and committed with revision 522683.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12880627" author="yunlee" created="Sun, 20 Jun 2010 13:59:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The current HoldCursorTest.java performs test on both embeded and client modes, however, I think it can not work correctly on client mode, actually, it still works in embeded mode. I have attached derby-2422-4.diff to correct this point, and the new.png and old.png showing the difference before and after my change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wish for reply!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12880812" author="knutanders" created="Mon, 21 Jun 2010 14:06:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Yun! That&apos;s a good catch. I&apos;ve committed your patch to trunk with revision 956559.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12881027" author="yunlee" created="Tue, 22 Jun 2010 03:43:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Knut. I have seen the new revision!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
